This function targets every record within a specified application's model. It then iterates over all existing primary keys and updates the corresponding target field using an external helper.

```python
def set_default_forwards(app_name, operation, apps, schema_editor):
    """Set default value for AleaIdField."""
    model = apps.get_model(app_name, operation.model_name)
    for obj_pk in model.objects.values_list('pk', flat=True):
        model.objects.filter(pk=obj_pk).update(**{
            operation.name: get_meteor_id(model, obj_pk),
        })
```

The function retrieves each record individually and updates it based on its primary key (PK), which ensures targeted modifications.
